CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 11, 1969, pg. 15 reads: "Holding Their Trophies and $1,000 checks are the three lucky winners of the Best Essays contest co-sponsored by the Quaker State Coca-Cola Bottling Co., and WAMO. The girls are from left; Juanita Wilson of Wylie Ave., Phyllis Hargrove, McKeesport, and Barbara Ann Robinson, Schenley Heights. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Four young women, including Juanita Wilson, Phyllis Hargrove, and Barbara Ann Robinson, holding trophies, standing with two men in interior in front of Coca Cola and cigarette machine
